\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director (as LASO)
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall serve as the final authority on audit logging requirements under this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall ensure configurations for systems processing Criminal Justice Information (CJI) meet the audit and accountability mandates of the FBI Criminal Justice Information Services (CJIS) Security Policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall retain non-delegable accountability for Local Agency Security Officer (LASO) obligations to the CJIS Systems Agency in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Data Governance and Classification Policy).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall approve exceptions to this policy in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Policy Implementation,
 Enforcement,
 and Legal Alignment).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall suspend automated and manual log disposition actions during active legal holds in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall review the meta-log of centralized log repository access on a quarterly basis to identify anomalous access patterns by authorized personnel.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
County Manager
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall approve policy exceptions that exceed the IT Director's delegated authority in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall serve as the escalation authority for enforcement disputes that cannot be resolved at the IT Director level.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assistant IT Director
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall oversee the centralized log management architecture.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall allocate audit record storage capacity sufficient to prevent logs from being overwritten or dropped prior to scheduled archival.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall ensure automated audit review mechanisms are configured to alert on anomalous activities in accordance with Section 6.5.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall ensure designated Tier L3 personnel conduct formal review of aggregated security audit logs no less than weekly,
 evidenced by a documented review record in the System of Engagement.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall initiate Problem record intake when weekly audit review identifies a pattern satisfying the Recurring Incident spawn trigger defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Problem Management Policy).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall coordinate response activities triggered by audit findings in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Incident Response Policy Overview) and 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Identification and Reporting Procedures).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
System and Network Administrators
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall configure information systems to generate required audit records in accordance with Section 6.1.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall forward audit records to the centralized log repository in accordance with Section 6.3.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall review automated security alerts within the service levels defined in Section 6.5.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall protect log facilities from unauthorized access in accordance with Section 6.4.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Constraint
\series default
:
 Personnel administering security access controls shall not modify or delete audit logs that record their own actions,
 nor serve as the sole reviewers of their own administrative logs,
 in accordance with the Separation of Duties Matrix maintained under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Delegation of Authority and Decision Rights).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Department Heads
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall identify business or regulatory logging requirements applicable to their departmental data.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall coordinate implementation of those requirements with the Information Operations Department.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
All County Personnel
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall not disable,
 bypass,
 or tamper with system auditing functions.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Compliance with this policy is mandatory for all Information Operations personnel and all County Personnel interacting with systems subject to this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assessment
\series default
:
 Adherence to this policy shall be assessed as part of the annual policy review and maturity scoring process defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Annual Policy Review and Maturity Scoring) and in accordance with the review schedule defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Policy Review and Update Procedures).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Enforcement
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall enforce compliance with this policy.
 Repeated non-compliance may be escalated under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions
\series default
:
 Exceptions to this policy shall be documented in writing with a business justification,
 compensating controls,
 and proposed duration,
 and shall be approved in accordance with the exception management framework established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 Oral exceptions are not valid.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Constraint
\series default
:
 No exception approved under this policy shall authorize the destruction or modification of audit records outside the retention and disposition framework of 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 nor the suspension of legal hold preservation obligations defined in Section 6.8 or Section 6.9.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Sanctions
\series default
:
 The following acts constitute severe security violations of this policy.
 Upon confirmed occurrence of any such act,
 the consequences defined in this bullet apply.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Prohibited Act — Tampering
\series default
:
 Disabling,
 bypassing,
 or tampering with audit logging mechanisms.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Prohibited Act — Record Destruction
\series default
:
 Unauthorized modification,
 deletion,
 or export of audit records.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Prohibited Act — Legal Hold Violation
\series default
:
 Failure to preserve audit records during an active legal hold,
 public records preservation requirement,
 audit,
 or incident investigation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Prohibited Act — Self-Review
\series default
:
 Serving as the sole reviewer of one's own administrative logs in violation of the Separation of Duties Constraint established in Section 3.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Immediate Access Revocation
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall direct the immediate revocation of the violating account's access in accordance with the Involuntary Termination procedure defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Access Control Policy).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Disciplinary Execution
\series default
:
 Disciplinary action shall be executed through the enforcement framework established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Conduct meeting the elements of NRS 205.4765 (Unlawful acts regarding computers) shall be referred for criminal prosecution through the County's legal process.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Universal Applicability
\series default
:
 This policy applies to all County information systems regardless of physical location,
 operational schedule,
 or delegation status.
\end_layout

