\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The accurate recording of system activity is essential to detecting unauthorized access,
 supporting forensic investigations,
 maintaining individual accountability,
 and satisfying the audit and accountability mandates of the CJIS Security Policy and Nevada Revised Statutes.
 This policy defines the requirements that govern the generation,
 protection,
 review,
 and retention of security audit logs,
 and establishes the routing by which audit findings enter the incident response,
 problem management,
 and compliance monitoring processes of the Information Operations Policy Manual.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Auditable Events
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall ensure County information systems,
 network infrastructure,
 and cloud environments are configured to generate audit records for security-relevant events.
 At a minimum,
 the following events shall be logged:
\end_layout

