\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Response to Audit Logging Process Failures
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Information Operations Department shall detect audit logging process failures and route them to the appropriate response process within defined time windows.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Failure Alerting
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall configure the logging system to alert the Assistant IT Director and designated administrators within one (1) hour of an audit logging process failure,
 including software or hardware errors,
 network disruption,
 and storage threshold breaches.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Restoration and Routing
\series default
:
 Designated Tier L3 Administrators shall,
 within one (1) hour of receiving the failure alert,
 either:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Confirm a benign operational cause — including disk capacity exhaustion,
 service crash,
 or network segment outage — and proceed with restoration under 
\series bold
Policy 
