 actions taken,
 and end-to-end verification results.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.7 Time Synchronization
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
To ensure accurate correlation of audit records across distinct systems,
 the System and Network Administrators shall synchronize all County information systems and network devices to an authoritative,
 County-approved Network Time Protocol (NTP) source.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Stratum-1 Source
\series default
:
 Primary internal NTP servers shall synchronize to Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) using a trusted,
 stratum-1 external time source.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
UTC Recording
\series default
:
 All County information systems shall record audit record timestamps in Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) to ensure cross-system and cross-jurisdictional forensic correlation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Timestamp Precision
\series default
:
 Audit record timestamps shall be recorded to hundredths-of-a-second precision,
 expressed in the format hh:mm:ss.ss.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Failure Handling
\series default
:
 Time synchronization failures shall be treated as audit logging process failures under Section 6.6.
\end_layout

